# Embed Guide — Next.js Pages Router

Generated by `/atw.embed` on {{generatedAt}}.

Answers captured in [`.atw/state/embed-answers.md`](../state/embed-answers.md).

---

## 1. Copy the bundle into `public/`

```bash
cp dist/widget.js public/widget.js
cp dist/widget.css public/widget.css
```

## 2. Load the widget from `_document.tsx`

```tsx
import Document, { Html, Head, Main, NextScript } from "next/document";

export default class MyDocument extends Document {
  render() {
    return (
      <Html lang="{{locale}}">
        <Head>
          <link rel="stylesheet" href="/widget.css" />
        </Head>
        <body>
          <Main />
          <NextScript />
          <script
            src="/widget.js"
            defer
            data-backend-url="{{backendUrl}}"
            data-api-base-url="{{apiBaseUrl}}"
            data-auth-mode="{{authMode}}"
{{#if authTokenKey}}            data-auth-token-key="{{authTokenKey}}"
{{/if}}            data-launcher-position="bottom-right"
            data-locale="{{locale}}"
{{#if loginUrl}}            data-login-url="{{loginUrl}}"
{{/if}}          />
        </body>
      </Html>
    );
  }
}
```

## 3. CORS on your host API

Configure your host API to return:

- `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: <your storefront origin>`
- `Access-Control-Allow-Methods: GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE, OPTIONS`
- `Access-Control-Allow-Headers: Content-Type, Authorization`
{{#if (eq authMode "cookie")}}- `Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true`
{{/if}}

## 4. CORS on the ATW backend

```env
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://your-storefront.example.com
```

## 5. Theming

Override CSS custom properties on your storefront:

```css
:root {
{{#if themePrimary}}  --atw-primary-color: {{themePrimary}};
{{/if}}{{#if themeRadius}}  --atw-radius: {{themeRadius}};
{{/if}}{{#if themeFont}}  --atw-font-family: {{themeFont}};
{{/if}}
}
```

